lenders.name: Barbara & Michael
lenders.loan_because: We have been in need many times ourselves. Before we met and married, my wife was a single mother, working hard to raise her children, and I lived overseas and both experienced and saw the gravity of extreme need. My wife and I  realize that many people, given the opportunity, will reach for and achieve greater things, they just need a chance. We want to be a part of giving that chance, we want to give others the opportunities that we have been given, we want to help.
lenders.occupational_info: My wife and I are  public school teachers. We love making a difference in others' lives.

lenders.name: Regina
lenders.loan_because: I just read the book Creating The World Without Poverty by Muhammad Yunus and it made me wish to partake in microfinance. I am ever so grateful to Kiva to give me this opportunity to reach out to someone on the other side of the globe.
lenders.occupational_info:
I am what is called a "Doll-Artist". For the last 28 years, my husband and I have been designing and making our own brand of  wood and porcelain dolls in our studio and we are very lucky indeed that collectors appreciate and collect them. Since most people find it hard to imagine what an artist-made doll could look like: here is a picture of a wood doll of our production. 
I am an elderly lady with grey hair now, but looked a little bit like this doll when I was a child. ;=)
